Program: Outlook
Title: 22/08/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00wt2py
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 23 Aug 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, we hear from a woman who's part of the first high-profile transgender couple in Peru and has just won the legal right to change her formerly male name to a female name. Also today, why teenagers in the American state of Maine are getting lessons in Middle East style diplomacy. And one of India's youngest female mayors explains why she ditched corporate life to go back to her village roots. Show less